<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1929-05-03T16:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1929-05-03T16:00:00-05:00" n="101" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d101">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">868.76/11: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Chargé in Greece</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Goold</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1929-05-03T17:00:00-04:00">May 3, 1929—5
                                p.m.</date></dateline></opener>
                        <p>21. Your 34, May 2, 5 p.m. Department approves of request made in your
                            letter to Mr. Venizelos and wishes you to continue to accord every
                            appropriate assistance in this matter.</p>
                        <p>Please keep Department promptly informed of further developments.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Stimson</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>